The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 November is 109,414 (12,610.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 November, there were 5,212 new confirmed cases (600.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 November, there were 4,660 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 12% (552 extra cases).
